  
We are seeking an experienced Business Analyst with a background in the Public
sector, adept at working across the product delivery lifecycle. The ideal
candidate will have a proven track record of translating business needs into
technical solutions, facilitating analysis sessions, and collaborating
effectively within an agile multidisciplinary team.  
** Key Responsibilities: **   

  * Work across the product delivery lifecycle, aligning business needs with technical capabilities to define solutions that deliver value. 
  * Facilitate analysis sessions, extracting critical requirements from stakeholders. 
  * Clearly explain analysis to Developers, QAs, Product Managers, and assurance specialists throughout the analysis cycle. 
  * Collaborate with User-Centered Design colleagues to shape and iterate service design using agile principles. 
  * Break down epics into user stories, collaborating with technical colleagues and subject matter experts to deliver outcome-focused solutions. 
  * Ensure user stories align with application architecture and security principles. 
  * Work within an agile multidisciplinary team of Developers, Designers, and QAs. 
  * Collaborate with developers to ensure effective implementation of user stories. 
  * Work with QA colleagues to develop tests and support quality assurance. 
  * Ensure completed stories are signed-off by the Product Manager. 
  * Facilitate estimation and prioritization sessions with the team. 
  * Maintain an audit trail of delivering user needs and business requirements through tools like Jira. 
  * Document analysis, questions, assumptions, and processes using appropriate tools such as Confluence. 
  * Work with the BA team and wider analysis community to ensure high-quality delivery. 
  * Actively participate in continuous learning and improvement of analysis processes. 
** Requirements: **   

  * Previous experience in a similar role 
  * GDS/Public sector experience 
  * Strong experience in working with agile methodologies. 
  * Proven ability to break down epics into user stories and develop acceptance criteria. 
  * Excellent communication and collaboration skills. 

